description.narrative: CHILDREN'S RIGHTS TO A SUPPORTIVE FAMILY ENVIRONMENT AND TO BE PROTECTED FROM VIOLENCE - Increased quality and quantity of social workers per 100,000 population to prevent and respond to abandonment, violence against children and exclusion, with a focus on the most vulnerable and especially children with disabilities., which contributes to Access To Justice, Cross-Sectoral Planning And Programme Reviews, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Partners supported to provide supportive and caring environment for all children, especially the most vulnerable, focusing on prevention measures

description.narrative: The RO supported countries to scale up strategic social work and social service workforce engagement. Serbia hosted a sub-regional conference on social work in the Western Balkans. The RO developed a partnership with Columbia University to support the development of social work competencies. The 2021-2027 financial framework of the EU continues to contain important language around De-Institutionalization (the regional flagship). The RO CP section signed a contract with the European Commission to support the Slovak Republic with their De-I monitoring framework; and secured agreement with the EU for UNICEF to pilot a Child Guarantee in Europe. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:03/02/2020
